_:fa28a9a564b330b63835cfd9b30661a0 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "10th /16th century (d. 973 / 1565)Famous scholar and prolific writer of the Šāfiʿī school. He studied the usual branches of Islamic and Arabic learning, and also medicine. While still a child, he lost his father and then his grandfather, but his father’s teachers, Šams al-Dīn b. Abī al-Ḥamāʾil (d. 932/1526), a noted mystic, and Šams al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Šanāwī, a disciple of this last, looked after his maintenance and education.\n               " .
